I’d like to talk about a job that I wouldn’t like to do, which is being a food delivery driver.

I first became aware of this job about six years ago when I moved to Ho Chi Minh City for my studies. At that time, I was overwhelmed by the heavy traffic, and I noticed many people riding motorbikes all day delivering food.

Later on, I did some research and found out that they were food delivery drivers. I also had a chance to talk to one of them, and he told me that he didn’t really enjoy the job, but he had to continue doing it to support his family. That conversation really stayed with me.

One reason I wouldn’t like this job is because of the health and safety risks. Drivers often have to work long hours, sometimes up to 12 or 14 hours a day, which can be exhausting. They also spend most of their time on the road, which increases the risk of accidents. In addition, some rely on energy drinks to stay awake, which isn’t good for their health in the long run.

Another reason is the working schedule. They usually have to work during weekends and holidays, so they don’t have much time to spend with their families or friends, which I think is a big disadvantage.

Overall, although this job plays an important role in society, I don’t think it’s suitable for me because of the pressure and the lifestyle.
